Did it work?

121
00:08:21,291 --> 00:08:24,057
Okay, you can come
on out, Neji!

122
00:08:28,024 --> 00:08:30,524
Behold the
explosion of youth!

123
00:08:30,557 --> 00:08:34,457
What are you,
crazy!? He looks
just like Guy
Sensei now!

124
00:08:34,491 --> 00:08:36,424
One...two...
three... four...

125
00:08:36,457 --> 00:08:38,124
Lee, what did
you do!?

126
00:08:38,157 --> 00:08:39,824
I am not sure!

127
00:08:39,857 --> 00:08:43,457
I was concentrating
with all my might on
Neji, but I guess I
missed the mark a little.

128
00:08:43,491 --> 00:08:46,224
Anyway, it looks
like this method
is effective!

129
00:08:52,157 --> 00:08:53,291
Huh?

130
00:08:55,224 --> 00:08:57,324
<i>(Lee)</i>
<i>Next up..! A quiet</i>
<i>hard worker who never</i>
<i>neglected her training-</i>

131
00:08:57,357 --> 00:09:00,057
<i>-and Kiba and Shino,</i>
<i>her loyal friends!</i>

132
00:09:04,824 --> 00:09:07,224
<i>Come back...!</i>

133
00:09:09,391 --> 00:09:14,891
Uhhh....

134
00:09:14,924 --> 00:09:16,791
Behold! The
explosion of youth!

135
00:09:16,824 --> 00:09:18,757
Not again!!!

136
00:09:18,791 --> 00:09:22,224
Why do all your
mistakes turn them
into Guy Sensei!?

137
00:09:22,257 --> 00:09:26,991
It looks like Guy Sensei
maintains an inordinately
large presence in my
subconscious...

138
00:09:27,824 --> 00:09:33,157
<i>Guy Sensei is always with</i>
<i>me... The stronger the</i>
<i>emotion... the more</i>
<i>entrenched he becomes...</i>

139
00:09:35,557 --> 00:09:40,024
Then you should probably
include Guy Sensei in
your thought and think
of everyone!

140
00:09:40,057 --> 00:09:41,157
Oh--

141
00:09:41,191 --> 00:09:44,057
go ahead, Lee.
Wish to return
to our old friends!

142
00:09:47,057 --> 00:09:48,024
Hm.

143
00:09:49,157 --> 00:09:51,091
<i>I do not want this</i>
<i>to go on any longer...</i>

144
00:09:51,124 --> 00:09:54,457
<i>I... I want to go</i>
<i>back to everyone!</i>

145
00:10:09,491 --> 00:10:10,924
[groan]

146
00:10:18,491 --> 00:10:21,457
Tht was just like
the first time...

147
00:10:21,491 --> 00:10:24,091
Huh!? Guys??

148
00:10:25,257 --> 00:10:27,357
(Tenten)
You're back to normal!

149
00:10:30,891 --> 00:10:34,424
(Tenten)
Oh no! Everyone
is Guy Sensei now!

150
00:10:34,457 --> 00:10:38,857
(Tenten)
Oh! Even the
normal villagers!?

151
00:10:38,891 --> 00:10:41,524
Lee! This is
ridiculous!

152
00:10:41,557 --> 00:10:44,157
What!? Guy Sensei!?

153
00:10:44,191 --> 00:10:46,124
What are you
talking about?
It is me!

154
00:10:46,157 --> 00:10:48,891
You wear the exact
same outfits...!!

155
00:10:48,924 --> 00:10:51,957
Jeez, now your
face looks like
his, too!

156
00:10:51,991 --> 00:10:55,257
Don't tell me!
Argh! I'm Guy
Sensei, too!

157
00:10:55,291 --> 00:10:59,924
Make it stop!
Standards and practices is
gonna yank us off the air!

158
00:10:59,957 --> 00:11:01,924
Behold! The explosion
of youth!

159
00:11:01,957 --> 00:11:03,391
To youth!

160
00:11:03,424 --> 00:11:06,491
Get away from me!
W-why is this
happening!?

161
00:11:06,524 --> 00:11:09,991
I just wanted to
know about the movie,
is that so terrible!?

162
00:11:10,924 --> 00:11:15,957
<i>(Narrator)</i>
<i>Heh, of course not!</i>
<i>But you should know,</i>
<i>the movie is called-</i>

163
00:11:20,891 --> 00:11:23,857
