not what the movie
is called at all!!!

165
00:11:28,057 --> 00:11:31,457
(bird chirping)
Idiot..! Idiot..! Idiot..!

166
00:11:43,948 --> 00:11:49,148
<i>(Narrator)</i>
<i>Now then, we're all well</i>
acquainted with the theatrics of
<i>Team Guy here, but you have--</i>

167
00:11:49,181 --> 00:11:51,448
It's my theatrical
feature! Their theatrics!

168
00:11:51,881 --> 00:11:55,881
<i>(Narrator)</i>
<i>Well, Rock Lee and his</i>
<i>pals are just as excited</i>
<i>as you are!</i>

169
00:11:55,915 --> 00:11:58,481
Neji! Were you
able to score
some tickets!?

170
00:11:58,515 --> 00:12:02,515
Oh yeah. The entire
Hyuga clan is planning
on attending it together.

171
00:12:04,648 --> 00:12:06,915
Our advance-sale
tickets are in hand!

172
00:12:06,948 --> 00:12:08,915
Neji! Lee! We've
got a problem!

173
00:12:08,948 --> 00:12:10,881
What's wrong?

174
00:12:10,915 --> 00:12:13,648
Something just went
down with Lady Tsunade!

175
00:12:14,681 --> 00:12:16,081
What?!!

176
00:12:16,115 --> 00:12:19,615
You're telling me that
the movie is still
missing a critical piece!?

177
00:12:20,515 --> 00:12:22,581
And it's something
big, too...

178
00:12:23,581 --> 00:12:25,615
That definitely
doesn't sound good!

179
00:12:25,648 --> 00:12:27,548
It's lacking
something major!

180
00:12:27,581 --> 00:12:32,015
So there is some kind
of problem with the film.
I wonder what...

181
00:12:38,681 --> 00:12:42,515
"The Amazing True Story
of the Leaf Village Film
Festival"

182
00:12:42,881 --> 00:12:44,148
Hmmm...

183
00:12:44,181 --> 00:12:46,581
Gee. guys, I wonder
what's missing...

184
00:12:46,615 --> 00:12:47,748
Ah!

185
00:12:47,781 --> 00:12:51,748
I think I have
got this whole
problem figured
out!

186
00:12:51,781 --> 00:12:55,048
[sirens]

187
00:12:55,081 --> 00:12:55,948
[machine gun blasts]

188
00:12:55,981 --> 00:12:57,748
[people screaming]

189
00:12:57,781 --> 00:12:59,581
[gun blasts]

190
00:13:00,781 --> 00:13:03,848
<i>(thinking)</i>
<i>Man, I have got</i>
<i>no luck at all!</i>

191
00:13:03,881 --> 00:13:11,581
<i>Here it is, Christmas</i>
<i>Eve, and I have got</i>
<i>to spend the night</i>
<i>rescuing my family!</i>

192
00:13:11,615 --> 00:13:12,548
[grunt]

193
00:13:17,081 --> 00:13:20,648
[screaming]

194
00:13:21,481 --> 00:13:22,581
What the heck
is going on?

195
00:13:22,615 --> 00:13:25,115
Why did we suddenly
get thrown into this
stupid skit!?

196
00:13:25,148 --> 00:13:27,448
But do you not
see, Tenten?!

197
00:13:27,481 --> 00:13:30,915
The movie is missing
one vital thing! A
Hollywood action
sequence!

198
00:13:30,948 --> 00:13:35,481
Carried out by a
gritty American
hero, overcoming all
the odds in style!

199
00:13:35,515 --> 00:13:38,548
We don't want that
kinda mess! An
American action star?

200
00:13:38,581 --> 00:13:40,815
<i>(Tenten)</i>
<i>Naruto's supposed</i>
<i>to be the hero here!</i>

201
00:13:40,848 --> 00:13:43,048
<i>(Tenten)</i>
<i>If you jump in like that,</i>
<i>you'll obliterate him!</i>

202
00:13:43,081 --> 00:13:46,715
It is fine! The
Movie's a compilation
of several arcs anyway!

203
00:13:46,748 --> 00:13:52,081
Oh yeah! What if the
mortal enemy he's fighting
against eventually turns out
to be his most powerful ally!?

204
00:13:53,648 --> 00:13:56,948
Are you out of
your mind, Lee!?
That'll ruin the
movie!!

205
00:13:56,981 --> 00:13:59,115
It's true, Lee,
she's right.

206
00:13:59,148 --> 00:14:01,081
Yo mean well, but
you're mixed up.

207
00:14:01,115 --> 00:14:05,081
We haven't had a
single movie that's
lacked in blockbuster
action!

208
00:14:05,115 --> 00:14:07,381
So then...! What
is missing, Neji!?

209
00:14:07,415 --> 00:14:11,948
Of course! It's so
obvious... the one
thing we're lacking...

210
00:14:13,615 --> 00:14:18,381
Oh Nejio, Nejio! Why
for art thou called
Nejio?

211
00:14:18,415 --> 00:14:22,381
Oh, Hinaette... My life
were better ended, then
death prolonged..!

