But the youths belonged
to houses steeped in
ancient grudge...

215
00:14:28,881 --> 00:14:34,448
Their misadventure
love doomed to fail,
they took matters
into their own hands!

216
00:14:34,481 --> 00:14:35,815
[grunt]

217
00:14:35,848 --> 00:14:38,948
Oh dearest Nejio!
I follow thee anon!

218
00:14:38,981 --> 00:14:39,981
[grunt]

219
00:14:40,548 --> 00:14:43,081
[church bells]

220
00:14:43,115 --> 00:14:46,081
Woah, hold the
phone, why do
we need this?

221
00:14:46,115 --> 00:14:48,548
A fair maiden and
fleeting romance!

222
00:14:48,581 --> 00:14:50,915
Two soul mates
fading into starry
night!

223
00:14:50,948 --> 00:14:54,848
It's obvious
what's missing! A
night of cinema
demands melodrama!

224
00:14:54,881 --> 00:14:59,015
This is a summer
blockbuster! No one
wants to see a tear
jerker right now!

225
00:14:59,048 --> 00:15:01,548
And we must bravely
shatter that mold!

226
00:15:01,581 --> 00:15:04,715
It'll be the most
powerful film in
history! Breaking
hearts far and wide.

227
00:15:04,748 --> 00:15:07,548
A timeless piece
that will forever
be a shining ex--

228
00:15:07,581 --> 00:15:09,781
Go shine out in
the stratosphere,
will ya!?

229
00:15:11,148 --> 00:15:14,048
I've been listening
to you guys, and you're
all totally clueless!

230
00:15:14,081 --> 00:15:16,748
Kiba!? Then you
are saying you
have a better
idea!?

231
00:15:16,781 --> 00:15:19,015
You bet we do!
Don't we, Hinata?

232
00:15:19,048 --> 00:15:20,948
Um... well...

233
00:15:20,981 --> 00:15:24,581
Maybe we're missing,
a ore innocent love,
you know..?

234
00:15:24,981 --> 00:15:27,881
<i>(Narrator)</i>
<i>Critics agree, it's the</i>
<i>greatest tearjerker of</i>
<i>the century...</i>

235
00:15:27,915 --> 00:15:30,481
<i>(Narrator)</i>
<i>Number one in</i>
<i>all Nations!</i>
<i>-Leaf Times.</i>

236
00:15:31,781 --> 00:15:34,015
<i>(Hinata)</i>
<i>With a young and</i>
<i>innocent love...</i>

237
00:15:34,048 --> 00:15:36,915
Huhhhh??

238
00:15:36,948 --> 00:15:38,181
[chuckle]

239
00:15:38,215 --> 00:15:43,881
A girl with no
courage... who
could only watch
him from afar...

240
00:15:46,481 --> 00:15:51,815
But she had to
change... so he
would finally
notice her...

241
00:15:57,648 --> 00:15:58,781
<i>(Hinata)</i>
<i>Welcome home!</i>

242
00:15:58,815 --> 00:16:02,148
ARGH!

243
00:16:02,181 --> 00:16:03,815
[sigh]

244
00:16:03,848 --> 00:16:04,848
Huh!?

245
00:16:05,815 --> 00:16:08,481
Whaaaa!?

246
00:16:10,481 --> 00:16:12,215
Uh...!

247
00:16:12,248 --> 00:16:15,848
<i>(Hinata)</i>
<i>I got that for you!</i>
<i>Please use it on</i>
<i>your sore muscles!</i>

248
00:16:15,881 --> 00:16:20,081
<i>(Hinata)</i>
<i>I've been watching you</i>
<i>since the day we met...</i>
<i>I still am...</i>

249
00:16:20,715 --> 00:16:25,381
[screams]

250
00:16:25,415 --> 00:16:28,048
<i>(Hinata)</i>
<i>I only have</i>
<i>eyes for you...</i>

251
00:16:32,115 --> 00:16:33,448
<i>[distant scream]</i>

252
00:16:33,481 --> 00:16:37,415
Uch, that's not innocent
love! That's a horror
film about a stalker!

253
00:16:37,448 --> 00:16:39,015
I'm not a
stalker!!

254
00:16:39,048 --> 00:16:42,415
That does it then!
It's my turn, and
I'll settle this
once and for all!

255
00:16:42,448 --> 00:16:44,415
Oh great, this
should be good.

256
00:16:46,081 --> 00:16:49,548
We live in a world
of conflict! One where
ninja face one brutal
mission after another!

257
00:16:49,581 --> 00:16:52,515
I know just what
we need.... Moe!

258
00:16:57,715 --> 00:17:00,348
[laugh] Come on,
Akamaru!

259
00:17:00,615 --> 00:17:02,448
[happy barking]

260
00:17:05,648 --> 00:17:10,915
[happy laughing]
Oh, you..!

261
00:17:10,948 --> 00:17:18,381
[happy laughing]

262
00:17:25,181 --> 00:17:27,681
[happy barking]

263
00:17:28,115 --> 00:17:30,715
Wait, only the
dog does cute!?

264
00:17:30,748 --> 00:17:33,681
Well, duh! Of course!
What could be cuter
than a dog, Tente--
ARGGHHHHHH!!!

265
00:17:33,715 --> 00:17:35,948
The audience
doesn't care!!!

266
00:17:35,981 --> 00:17:41,748
Guys, your preoccupation
with the superficial
has only blinded you...

267
00:17:41,781 --> 00:17:45,415
You've missed the one
crucial thing we've lacked.

268
00:17:45,448 --> 00:17:48,148
Man's inner most
thinking made clear...

269
00:17:48,181 --> 00:17:50,781
The voice of out
heart, singing out.

270
00:17:50,815 --> 00:17:53,915
(thinking)
Wow, that's Shino
for you! He's so
deep...

271
00:17:53,948 --> 00:17:58,848
<i>(Shino)</i>
<i>The weather was awful the day</i>
<i>we filmed this scene. I can't</i>
tell you how many takes we did.

272
00:17:58,881 --> 00:18:02,448
<i>We hit craft services for</i>
<i>lunch while we waited</i>
<i>for it to clear...</i>

273
00:18:02,481 --> 00:18:06,715
<i>...the spread was pretty</i>
<i>light on veggies, I really</i>
<i>had my mind set on salad</i>
<i>that day....</i>

274
00:18:06,748 --> 00:18:08,748
You meant "audio
commentary!?"

275
00:18:08,781 --> 00:18:10,115
There a problem
with that?

276
00:18:10,148 --> 00:18:12,015
I don't even know
where to start!

277
00:18:12,048 --> 00:18:14,381
You can't have audio
commentary in the
theatre!!!

278
00:18:14,415 --> 00:18:16,648
Look, it's you.

279
00:18:16,681 --> 00:18:20,981
Huh?! Yeah, you know, I really
wanted to get this scene just
right so we shot a ton of takes,
but at the end of the day--

280
00:18:21,015 --> 00:18:22,815
Don't drag me
into this!!!

281
00:18:22,848 --> 00:18:26,548
(sigh) I know that
we're missing something,
but what!?

282
00:18:26,581 --> 00:18:27,815
You fools!

283
00:18:27,848 --> 00:18:30,381
How can you ninnies
not see it!?

284
00:18:30,415 --> 00:18:32,515
Orochimaru? What
are you doing here?

285
00:18:32,548 --> 00:18:34,015
Just dropping in!

286
00:18:34,048 --> 00:18:36,948
We saw you idiots
flailing about over
here and couldn't
resist..!

287
00:18:36,981 --> 00:18:39,515
Wait, then you
know what the
movie is missing?

288
00:18:39,548 --> 00:18:43,415
Silly child, you're
completely forgetting
the obvious, it seems.

289
00:18:43,448 --> 00:18:46,081
Every film has one
essential element!

290
00:18:46,115 --> 00:18:50,681
One that must never
be overlooked... The
most important thing
of all!

291
00:18:51,115 --> 00:18:52,481
[gulps]

292
00:18:54,548 --> 00:18:56,781
Annnd... action!

293
00:18:56,815 --> 00:18:58,681
<i>(Orochimaru)</i>
<i>I turn forty</i>
<i>this year.</i>

294
00:18:58,715 --> 00:19:01,848
<i>I've spent my whole</i>
<i>career playing no-name</i>
<i>bit parts...</i>

295
00:19:01,881 --> 00:19:05,381
<i>I always considered</i>
<i>myself dedicated to</i>
<i>the craft...</i>

296
00:19:05,815 --> 00:19:09,815
<i>But one day I realized</i>
<i>that everyone around me</i>
<i>was half my age!</i>

297
00:19:09,848 --> 00:19:14,481
<i>I saw them land starring</i>
<i>roles, while I just spun</i>
<i>my wheels!</i>

298
00:19:15,615 --> 00:19:16,881
I'm... fired!?

299
00:19:16,915 --> 00:19:20,048
The thing is...
Everyone's having a
hard time working
with ya.

300
00:19:20,081 --> 00:19:22,715
He's taking the
job way too seriously!

301
00:19:22,748 --> 00:19:24,848
Cut! Cut, already!

302
00:19:24,881 --> 00:19:28,715
Well, Orosuke's a nice
guy ad all, but sometimes
he's a big pushy...

303
00:19:28,748 --> 00:19:30,148
(scream)

304
00:19:30,181 --> 00:19:31,048
The camera's
over here...

305
00:19:31,081 --> 00:19:33,015
(bar tender)
We're closing,
pal, go home.

306
00:19:33,048 --> 00:19:34,415
<i>(Orochimaru)</i>
<i>What'd you say</i>
<i>to me!?</i>

307
00:19:34,448 --> 00:19:35,881
(bar tender)
Alright! That's it!

308
00:19:36,181 --> 00:19:38,715
<i>(Orochimaru)</i>
<i>But even I found someone</i>
<i>who loved me...</i>

309
00:19:38,748 --> 00:19:42,981
<i>I met the sheltered daughter</i>
<i>of some bigwig who ran a film</i>
<i>distribution company...</i>

310
00:19:43,015 --> 00:19:47,848
<i>...and she fell for</i>
<i>a two-bit nobody like</i>
<i>me! Can you imagine?</i>

311
00:19:47,881 --> 00:19:50,115
<i>He objected, of</i>
<i>course, so we ran</i>
<i>off...</i>

312
00:19:50,148 --> 00:19:54,615
<i>...but before we'd had</i>
<i>a chance to create a</i>
<i>single memory together...</i>

313
00:19:54,648 --> 00:19:57,615
<i>Even common courtesy</i>
<i>runs out eventually...</i>

314
00:19:57,648 --> 00:20:01,681
[sigh]
"Went back to my
parents house" eh?

315
00:20:01,715 --> 00:20:03,548
Oh well...

316
00:20:05,681 --> 00:20:08,048
Sweetheart...
sweetheart?!

317
00:20:08,081 --> 00:20:11,415
You'e here... why?!

318
00:20:11,448 --> 00:20:13,781
Why don't you
try out for this?

319
00:20:14,881 --> 00:20:18,048
You asked your
father, didn't you?

320
00:20:18,081 --> 00:20:20,048
I had to...

321
00:20:20,081 --> 00:20:23,115
The first he did
was threaten to
disown me...

322
00:20:23,148 --> 00:20:26,915
But begging on my
knees was a small
price to pay.

323
00:20:27,848 --> 00:20:29,548
But why me...

324
00:20:29,581 --> 00:20:36,848
I've seen first hand.
I know how brightly
you shine when you're
in front of the camera.

325
00:20:36,881 --> 00:20:42,381
And I want that light
in my life every day!

326
00:20:43,181 --> 00:20:44,515
[gasp]

327
00:20:50,148 --> 00:20:53,515
Well this should be
good. Let's see what
you're made of, kid.

328
00:20:53,881 --> 00:20:56,881
I'll do it! No
matter what it
takes!!

329
00:20:56,915 --> 00:20:58,481
<i>(crew member)</i>
<i>Standby, everybody!</i>

330
00:20:58,515 --> 00:21:03,481
Alright! Just watch,
my beloved! I'm going
to shine brighter than
the sun for you!

331
00:21:06,115 --> 00:21:07,248
The hell!?

332
00:21:07,281 --> 00:21:09,815
Wait a minute, is
this an anti-
piracy commercial?

333
00:21:09,848 --> 00:21:13,381
Well, you'd be in
big trouble without.

334
00:21:13,415 --> 00:21:16,581
Yeah I suppose so.
But what's that have
to do with the story?

335
00:21:16,615 --> 00:21:19,481
Bravo, sir! You bring
such perspective!

336
00:21:19,515 --> 00:21:21,848
Your perspective
might be a little
skewed...

337
00:21:21,881 --> 00:21:25,115
Gimme a break! What
does this have to do
with stopping piracy!?

338
00:21:25,148 --> 00:21:28,481
Trust me, you'll
see! I'll explain
everything shortly!

339
00:21:28,515 --> 00:21:29,448
[grunt]

340
00:21:29,481 --> 00:21:32,081
[growling]

341
00:21:32,115 --> 00:21:33,148
ARGH!

342
00:21:33,181 --> 00:21:38,481
[cheering and shouting]

343
00:21:39,481 --> 00:21:43,948
<i>(Narrator)</i>
<i>Dear me. Well, Lady</i>
<i>Tsunade, what exactly</i>
<i>was missing?</i>

344
00:21:43,981 --> 00:21:46,681
It just arrived,
as a matter of fact!

345
00:21:53,681 --> 00:21:56,781
<i>(Tsunade)</i>
<i>Make sure you all see</i>
<i>the new Naruto Movie!</i>

346
00:21:56,815 --> 00:22:02,815
<i>(Narrator)</i>
<i>Ah, it was the movie poster!</i>
<i>Well, see you all at the</i>
<i>theaters, faithful viewers!</i>

347
00:22:02,848 --> 00:22:05,681
You've gotta be kidding
me! That was all pointless!?

348
00:23:47,416 --> 00:23:50,949
<i>(Neji)</i>
<i>Join us next time for</i>
<i>"Boom! The Shinobi</i>
<i>Fireworks Show,"</i>

349
00:23:50,982 --> 00:23:53,416
<i>(Neji)</i>
<i>and "Bang! Tenten's</i>
<i>Acting Weird!"</i>

350
00:23:53,449 --> 00:23:56,216
<i>(Tenten)</i>
<i>A fireworks show!?</i>
<i>I can't wait!</i>

351
00:23:56,249 --> 00:24:00,082
<i>(Shikamaru)</i>
<i>With everyone off seeing</i>
<i>the display, I can get in</i>
<i>a good nap.</i>

352
00:24:00,116 --> 00:24:03,182
<i>(Naruto)</i>
<i>I hear the ramen they</i>
<i>serve at those shows</i>
<i>is one of a kind!</i>

353
00:24:03,216 --> 00:24:07,249
<i>(Lee)</i>
<i>Sakura's going to look</i>
<i>to pretty with her face</i>
<i>lit up by the sparklers!</i>

354
00:24:07,282 --> 00:24:09,416
<i>(Tenten)</i>
<i>What about the actual</i>
<i>fireworks!?</i>

